features: 1. Paring Knife Set included: 1pcs 3.25 inch paring knife, 1pcs 3.25 inch serrated paring knife, 1pcs 5 inch utility knife. The cutting knife also comes with three matched knife cover, ensuring that your paring knives remain protected and easily accessible when not in use. With this pairing knife set, you'll have everything you need to slice, chop, and cut your way through any recipe with ease.

2. Versatile: The three pearing knife included in this set cover a wide range of cutting tasks, making them a versatile addition to any kitchen. The 3.25 inch paring knife is perfect for tasks such as peeling and coring fruits and vegetables, while the serrated paring knife is ideal for cutting through tough skins and rinds, such as those on tomatoes or citrus fruits. The 5 inch utility knife is a great all-purpose knife, suitable for a range of tasks from slicing sandwiches to trimming meat.

3. High-quality: The paring knives in this set are made from high-carbon German stainless steel, which is a durable and long-lasting material that is resistant to rust and corrosion. The blades are precision-forged for strength and sharpness, and the handles are made from quality PP materials that provide a comfortable and secure grip. The tomato knife are designed to withstand regular use and retain their sharpness over time.

4. Easy to use: The fruit knife in this set are designed to be easy to use, even for inexperienced cooks. The blades are sharp and precise, making it easy to cut through food with minimal effort. The handles are ergonomically designed to fit comfortably in your hand, reducing hand fatigue and improving control. The small knives are also lightweight, making them easy to maneuver and control.

5. WHAT YOU GOT: 1pcs 3.25 in paring knife, 1pcs 3.25 inch serrated paring knife, 1pcs 5 inch utility knife and 3 matched knife sheath. This paring knife set makes an excellent gift for anyone who enjoys cooking or is just starting to build their kitchen knife collection. The paring knife with sheath is a thoughtful and practical gift that is sure to be appreciated by anyone who receives it.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 11, 2024
Reviewed in the United States on August 28, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great for the price
reviews.reviewText: Can't beat these for 2 bucks a knife. The handles feel cheap, because they are cheap. But that's OK. These get the job done well. I don't know that I'd want to peel enough apples for a pie with one of these, but for most quick uses they are just fine. I don't have a dishwasher, so I don't know how they'd hold up to that. The only downside is that the plastic covers just slide right off too easily. Gravity will pull them off. But hey, for the price, at least they come with the sleeves.
